<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-17T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-17T10:00:00-05:00" n="183" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5881</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Special Agent</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi><note n="3" xml:id="d183fn3">Transmitted through the Ambassador
                                    in France, in telegram No. 2299.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-17T16:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your 2446, 14th. Please assure the President that nothing done or
                                said that in the remotest degree exceeds instructions. There is <pb facs="0205" n="131" xml:id="pg_131"/> no cause for the President
                                or you to feel disturbed. Under all the circumstances it is most
                                desirable that <persName>Frankfurter</persName> make a detailed
                                report orally. <persName>Frankfurter</persName> therefore will
                                return. I shall rest with my wife at Aix-les-Bains prepared to
                                proceed to Cairo if after hearing report of
                                    <persName>Frankfurter</persName> the President still desires me
                                to go.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgenthau</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>